        "\n",
        "## Module Learning Objectives\n",
        "\n",
        "By the end of Module 3, students should be able to:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. move from retrieval alone to retrieval plus prompting\n",
        "2. design prompts that stay grounded in retrieved evidence\n",
        "3. recognize when abstention is preferable to unsupported synthesis\n",
        "4. prepare prompt patterns for labs, assignments, and project work\n",
        "\n",
        "## Tutorial Learning Objectives\n",
        "\n",
        "This tutorial picks up where `M03_T1` leaves off.\n",
        "Instead of retrieving SEC chunks only, we now ask:\n",
        "\n",
        "- how should those chunks be passed into a prompt?\n",
        "- what instructions improve groundedness?\n",
        "- when should the model abstain?\n",
        "\n",
        "## How This Tutorial Connects\n",
        "\n",
        "- `M03_T1` provides the retrieval step.\n",
        "- `M03_Lab2` and `M03_A` depend on grounded prompt design.\n",
        "- `M03_Proj` can reuse these prompt patterns in a more complete pipeline.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Step 1: Example Retrieved Context"
      ],
      "id": "c32d0959"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "example_chunks = [\n",
        "    {\"chunk_id\": \"c1\", \"company\": \"ExampleCo\", \"item\": \"1A\",\n",
        "     \"text\": \"The company faces increasing cybersecurity risks and data privacy obligations.\"},\n",
        "    {\"chunk_id\": \"c2\", \"company\": \"ExampleCo\", \"item\": \"7\",\n",
        "     \"text\": \"Management discussed investments in digital infrastructure and internal systems.\"},\n",
        "]\n",
        "question = \"What technology-related risks are disclosed and how are they being addressed?\""
      ],
      "id": "62a28b8d",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Step 2: Build a Grounded Prompt"
      ],
      "id": "a72a71a2"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def make_grounded_prompt(question: str, chunks: list[dict]) -> str:\n",
        "    context = []\n",
        "    for i, c in enumerate(chunks, 1):\n",
        "        context.append(\n",
        "            f\"[Chunk {i} | {c['company']} | Item {c['item']} | {c['chunk_id']}]\\n{c['text']}\"\n",
        "        )\n",
        "    joined = \"\\\\n\\\\n\".join(context)\n",
        "    return f\\\"\\\"\\\"You are a financial analysis assistant.\n",
        "Use only the retrieved SEC evidence below.\n",
        "If the answer is not supported, say that the evidence is insufficient.\n",
        "\n",
        "Question:\n",
        "{question}\n",
        "\n",
        "Retrieved context:\n",
        "{joined}\n",
        "\n",
        "Answer with short citations to the chunk labels.\\\"\\\"\\\"\n",
        "\n",
        "print(make_grounded_prompt(question, example_chunks))"
      ],
      "id": "0af5ee02",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Step 3: Compare Weak vs Strong Prompting"
      ],
      "id": "8f070641"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "weak_prompt = f\"Answer this question: {question}\"\n",
        "strong_prompt = make_grounded_prompt(question, example_chunks)\n",
        "print(\"Weak prompt length:\", len(weak_prompt))\n",
        "print(\"Strong prompt length:\", len(strong_prompt))"
      ],
      "id": "24da336f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
