        "## Step 4: Prompt Design Checklist\n",
        "\n",
        "A strong retrieval-grounded prompt should:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. define the assistant role\n",
        "2. restrict the model to retrieved evidence\n",
        "3. instruct abstention when evidence is weak\n",
        "4. require citations or provenance markers\n",
        "5. keep context organized and easy to scan\n",
        "\n",
        "## Why This Matters\n",
        "\n",
        "This tutorial is intentionally close to `M03_Lab1` and the module assignment logic:\n",
        "\n",
        "- retrieval quality matters\n",
        "- prompt structure matters\n",
        "- groundedness matters\n",
        "\n",
        "The combination of retrieval plus careful prompting becomes the foundation for later RAG work in Modules 5 and the final project.\n",
